{"batchcomplete": "", "query": {"pages": {"22872100": {"pageid": 22872100, "ns": 0, "title": "The House of the Devil (2009 film)", "contentmodel": "wikitext", "pagelanguage": "en", "pagelanguagehtmlcode": "en", "pagelanguagedir": "ltr", "touched": "2026-02-26T18:54:16Z", "lastrevid": 1340000399, "length": 20428, "fullurl": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_House_of_the_Devil_(2009_film)", "editurl": "https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=The_House_of_the_Devil_(2009_film)&action=edit", "canonicalurl": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_House_of_the_Devil_(2009_film)", "pageprops": {"defaultsort": "House of the Devil, The", "displaytitle": "<i>The House of the Devil</i> (2009 film)", "page_image": "The_House_of_the_Devil.jpg", "wikibase-shortdesc": "2009 film by Ti West", "wikibase_item": "Q1984765"}, "description": "2009 film by Ti West", "descriptionsource": "local", "extract": "The House of the Devil is a 2009 American horror film written, directed, and edited by Ti West, starring Jocelin Donahue, Tom Noonan, Mary Woronov, Greta Gerwig, A. J. Bowen, and Dee Wallace.\nThe plot concerns a young college student who is hired as a babysitter at an isolated house and is soon caught up in bizarre and dangerous events as she fights for her life.\nThe film combines elements of both the slasher film and haunted house subgenres while using the \"satanic panic\" of the 1980s as a central plot element. It pays homage to the style of horror films of the 1970s and 1980s by using filmmaking techniques and technology commonly employed at the time. The opening text claims that the film is based on true events, a practice used in horror films such as The Texas Chain Saw Massacre (1974) and The Amityville Horror (1979).", "categories": [{"ns": 14, "title": "Category:2000s supernatural horror films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:2009 American films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:2009 English-language films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:2009 films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "C